<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="561" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/19000:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Poughkeepsie</hi>, N. Y.</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-07">January 7,
                                1942</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your cable from Childs, Tangier, number 4, January 5th. I am inclined to
                            agree with his suggestion about Orgaz. What can you work out on
                            this.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>